Description: *Steps to Reproduce:*  # Log in to the BB app on an iOS device. # Add a prescription item to the cart. # Click on *Proceed* to reach the Prescription Upload page. # Tap the *device back button* to go back. # When the bottom sheet appears, tap on *Resume Upload*.  *Actual Result:* The app becomes unresponsive (freezes) after tapping *Resume Upload* from the bottom sheet.  *Expected Result:* The app should smoothly navigate back to the Prescription Upload page without freezing.  Video link: [https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1iKPWQ2Rqxhs6uS25MnHq3gJCTYp5gQVu|https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1iKPWQ2Rqxhs6uS25MnHq3gJCTYp5gQVu|smart-link]

Summary: [Prod-issue][Android]- the user is redirected to the Product Listing page instead of the Basket when clicking Proceed while the page is still loading. on pressing the device back button
Description: *Steps to Reproduce:*  # Log in to the BB app. # Add a product to the cart. # Navigate to the Basket page. # While the Basket page is still loading, quickly click on the *Proceed* button. # Observe the navigation flow. # Press the *device back button*.  *Actual Result:*  * User is taken back to the Product Listing (PL) page instead of the expected navigation to the Basket. * Device back button behavior is inconsistent and may lead to unexpected screens.  *Expected Result:*  * Device back button should return the user to the correct previous screen based on the flow.

Summary: Paper bag suggestion is not happening as expected in a specific case
Description: Steps to simulate :   1.  Place a bbnow order involving 2 skus belonging to PST1 and PST2 respectively 2.  Make sure that both PST1 and PST2 have override_container_category set to PAPERBAG 3.  Order volume including sku1 and sku2 should be such that it can be fitted in Large Bag 4.  In this case, pick_opst_group_container_estimate should have 2 entries one for each PST, PST1 and PST2 and one of the PST1 (of larger volume) should have paper bag recommendation in meta_info along with container_type being set to one of the paper bags (s/m/l) and other PST, PST2 should have no paper bag recommendation as part of meta_info instead should have merge_required field set to true and normal container_type populated  But the same is not happening for both PSTS, paper bag recommendations are coming  NOTE :   a) Have attached screenshots for reference b) Order id : 1614725074

Summary: [Realtime Earning] Cache update happening before Ratecard update sync
Description: → Existing:   on ratecard change, immediately cache is cleared for payout api and the recalculation happens for particular cee associated with the rate_card.  this recalculation will pick the details from clickhouse but it could be possible that sync has not happened yet for rate_card change.  so possibly, it would again pick the older rate_Card and put it in cache. this will create problem.    → Expected:  the ratecard changes should be reflected and cache should pick the appropriate rate card update.

Summary: Call 742585 - S3 BB :Negative Wallet Balance Not Restricting Orders
Description: # MyMCS                       : 742585  # Issue Reported Date   : 14-APR-25          # Location                      :  PAN india  # Issue Reported by and Dep : CS B2C  # Issue severity              : S3  # Issue type                  :  Complaint  # Location Impacted      : PAN india  # Issue Reported           :  Negative Wallet Balance Not Restricting Orders    # L1 Analysis                 :       We have identified an issue where a customer is taking advantage of a negative wallet balance by carrying forward the same negative amount to the next order and subsequently cancelling that order.  *As pr BB Wallet 2.0 - Fraud Check*  A threshold value will be defined in the new system. Users will not be allowed to cross this value. Say Rs -500 is the value, then users will have to clear -500 in bbwallet, only then they can place a new order. User can be blocked from placing order in 2 cases *Case 1:* If user has negative balance in bbwallet >=  threshold amount *Case 2:* If user has open COD order with negative bbwallet amount such that negative bbwallet >= threshold amount.   Please find the customer's wallet details below for your reference.    PPT Drive link: [https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1cgvRPpX7yrhMDD6FsuFQ37UbURdLpBEPRJvLmxsR-Eg/edit#slide=id.g24fcc6c0f8d_0_30|https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1cgvRPpX7yrhMDD6FsuFQ37UbURdLpBEPRJvLmxsR-Eg/edit#slide=id.g24fcc6c0f8d_0_30|smart-link]

Summary: For the Search term ='cat food', In the Quick Filter position we introduced multiple tag groups and tag values. When clicking on one of the tag values as a quick filter, all the tag values of the other tag groups disappear except the selected one.
Description: I will share the tag group and tag values with their IDs in detail. here is the list of tag groups and tag value for reference:- Tag Value                 Tag group           (both tag value ID number & tag group ID number are in the brackets) Cat(6191)                 pet(483) Adult Cat(6189)	pet lifestage(484) Kitten(6193)	        pet lifestage(484) Chicken(6194)         meal base(485) Tuna(6195)              meal base(485) Wet Food(6196)      food form(486) Dry Food(6198)	food form(486) Non Veg(6197)        dietary choice(487) Attached a google drive link of a video clicking through the tag values & how the other tag group’s tag values disappear for your reference. The search term where these tags were uploaded is ‘cat food’.    [https://drive.google.com/file/d/16yOGJfbW9y1TYpnBpDRt-HvNwflyXKhD/view?usp=sharing|https://drive.google.com/file/d/16yOGJfbW9y1TYpnBpDRt-HvNwflyXKhD/view?usp=sharing|smart-embed]       So basically when i search for cat food all the tag values show up, once i click on chicken only the tag group meal base values stay in the quick filter position, so chicken & tuna, similarly when i click on dry food only dry food, wet food are present on the quick filter position after clicking on a quick filter position. Need a resolution where of course the tag values from the same tag group stay together in the first positions after clicking on it, but i want rest of the tag values to appear after them even after a tag value from another tag group is clicked on.

Summary: [Realtime Earning] Incorrect order milestone payout calculation logic
Description: currently '{{order_incentive_payouts}}' display incorrect value for milestone incentives.   code :   {noformat} ""incentives_milestones"": {                         ""daily"": [                             {                                 ""index"": 0,                                 ""target"": 6,                                 ""rate"": 10.0,                                 ""total"": 60.0,                                 ""is_incremental"": false                             },{noformat}  Daily incentive scenario*:* '{{is_incremental}}' = false or *flat incentive.*           → existing logic : we would be assigning the rate value based on the target that is achieved.           → point to be discussed : should we add the rate based on milestone once it is achieved or only the rate value associated to target should be displayed.                ex: there are 3 milestones  ( [target : 6, rate : 10], [target: 10, rate : 20], [target: 20, rate 40])  * with current logic, if cee had delivered 20 orders, we are adding the value 40. or should we add the rate values, 10 + 20 + 40 = 70.   Daily incentive scenario : '{{is_incremental}}' = true or *incremental incentive*  → existing logic : ‘rate’ * ‘target’ value is considered on the orders that are delivered.  → point to be discussed : we should be assigning the incremental value from the next order of target value.        ex : cee achieves incremental milestone for delivering 10 orders.  so as per current logic, we are giving cee : 10 * rate value and then on upcoming orders, he will be get rate value added to each delivered order.   expected behavior is to include rate value on the upcoming orders only. i.e: 11th order will get extra rate value.   weekly incremental scenario : cee achieves weekly incremental milestone, in this the incremental value should be displayed along with realtime earning for that day.

Summary: CEE payout [Realtime Earning] : Newly onboarded Cee is not able to see realtime earning on first day.
Description: scenario:   → new cee gets onboarded in payout system, initially store doesn’t get assigned and hence no rate is applicable. so on first day, for the order he/she delivers, no realtime earning would be reflected.   However, from day 2 the earnings would be shown since we would have order report parsed in system and from that report, we would assign the store to the cee.   Expectation:  → cee should be assigned with store on first day itself in order to get realtime earning be displayed.   possible solution:   → while onboarding the cee in payout, we should be assigning the store as well.

Summary: For otc skus, empty tag value is getting created on sku upload and same is seen in solr.
Description: Problem: For otc skus, empty tag value is getting created on sku upload and same is seen in solr.  Steps to reproduce:  # Do an sku upload for an sku with prescription_required: false and virtual_consultation: false in the additional_info in the template. # Check if entry is created in product_productdescription_product_tags for that sku and what are these tags in tag_tagvalue.  Expected:  If the sku is an otc i.e it has prescription_required: false and virtual_consultation: false, then no entry in product_productdescription_product_tags with group as prescription-details should be created for it.   Actual: Currently, we see tag group as prescription-details and tag value as empty and same is seen in solr.

Summary: [Realtime Earning] order replay cron issue : incorrect counter value
Description: for failed orders, the counter value is set to 3 initially. on each cron run, the counter value should be reduced by 1 indicating it processed. however if the order is still failed, again cron would pick up. on counter value 0, the order should not be considered by cron anymore.   but here, we observed the counter value goes well below zero indicating the order is still being picked by order replay cron. attached screenshot for reference:  !image-20250403-053434.png|width=1558,height=155,alt=""image-20250403-053434.png""!  we can see multiple messages in topic related to order replay in QA.   !image-20250403-053523.png|width=1764,height=814,alt=""image-20250403-053523.png""!    order id : 1614715530

Summary: 741534 | BBI | BBInstant LCD Campaign Push Issue
Description: Hi Jugal/Puri/Akash,  The BBInstant marketing team pushed two campaigns (*Drools* and *TATA_Coffee*) on *April 1st*. However, out of *2043 locations*, the campaigns are active in only *183 locations*.  We have attempted troubleshooting on our end and did not find any specific errors in *publisher.log, publish.log, or redisWorker.log*. However, we observed that around *400 locations* failed to establish a connection with Salt. Apart from this, no major errors were identified, and there were no issues logged with *RedisWorker*.  We suspect that:  * *RedisWorker is pushing campaigns very slowly.* * *It is also including expired campaigns in the push process* (we are unsure if this is expected behavior).  As brands are escalating this issue, we need your assistance in resolving it at the earliest. Could you please look into this and help us address the problem?  Looking forward to your response.  CC : [~accountid:5c7775a332e60d5a276b4fb6]   Regards,  Vineetha R
